@startuml Option1_EventBased_Overview

title Option 1: Event-based ParameterSet Distribution (mw::com IPC)

participant "Filesystem" as FS
participant "ParameterSetCollection" as PSC
participant "ConfigDaemon" as ConfigDaemon
participant "mw::com Skeleton\n(ParameterSetEventServicePPort)" as Skeleton
database "Shared Memory" as SHM
participant "mw::com Proxy" as Proxy
participant "ConfigProvider" as CP

== Initialization ==

ConfigDaemon -> FS : read payload size from\n buffer_size_needs.json
FS --> ConfigDaemon : payload size
ConfigDaemon -> Skeleton : create Skeleton with each ParameterSet\n as a separate event service port
Skeleton -> SHM : allocate shared memory\n(2 slots per ParameterSet event)

== Runtime: ParameterSet Update ==

ConfigDaemon -> Skeleton: OfferService

CP -> Proxy : subscribe to ParameterSet events\n(by registered name)
Proxy -> Skeleton
Skeleton --> Proxy
Proxy --> CP

PSC -> Skeleton : send(event) for each ParameterSet
Skeleton -> SHM : write event data\n(slot 0 or slot 1)
SHM --> Skeleton
Skeleton --> PSC


CP -> Proxy : GetParameterSet()
Proxy -> SHM : GetNewSamples()
SHM --> Proxy : return new samples
Proxy --> CP : filter and get the latest\nsample for the requested ParameterSet

@enduml
